um_comments":51,"objectID":"48332151","points":65,"story_id":48332151,"title":"Perry Compiles TypeScript directly to executables using SWC and LLVM","updated_at":"2026-05-30T07:13:39Z","url":"https://www.perryts.com/"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"satvikpendem"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Ember.js 7.0"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://blog.emberjs.com/ember-released-7-0/"}},"_tags":["story","author_satvikpendem","story_48330902","front_page"],"author":"satvikpendem","children":[48331022,48331298,48331656,48332227,48332838,48333318],"created_at":"2026-05-29T23:57:45Z","created_at_i":1780099065,"num_comments":8,"objectID":"48330902","points":56,"story_id":48330902,"title":"Ember.js 7.0","updated_at":"2026-05-30T07:03:24Z","url":"https://blog.emberjs.com/ember-released-7-0/"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"arrdalan"},"story_text":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Hey everyone,<p>I previously introduced an open source private home security camera in 2024, which uses OpenMLS for end-to-end encryption: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42284412\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42284412</a>.<p>It was called Privastead then and it's now renamed to Secluso.<p>John Kaczman found my project from here and has been working on it with me over the last year and half. We've made a lot of improvements to the software, which we would like to share with you:<p>- You can now set this up on your Raspberry Pi in less than 5 minutes with no technical expertise using our easy-to-use GUI deploy tool. We've put together a comprehensive build-your-own guide that walks you through the required steps (you can find a link at the top of the repository README).<p>- We use a customized, minimal OS based on the Yocto project for the camera.<p>- Every part of our stack except for the iOS app has reproducible builds. This includes our Android app, camera/server binaries, deploy tool, and the aforementioned OS.<p>- We've re-designed our mobile app, which is now on the iOS App Store and Google Play store.<p>- We now support UnifiedPush for more privacy-preserving push notifications.<p>Looking forward to seeing what you all think!"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Show HN: Open-source private home security camera system (end-to-end encryption)"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://github.com/secluso/core"}},"_tags":["story","author_arrdalan","story_48330192","show_hn","front_page"],"author":"arrdalan","children":[48330420,48330966,48331075,48331439,48331671,48331806,48333403],"created_at":"2026-05-29T22:32:29Z","created_at_i":1780093949,"num_comments":10,"objectID":"48330192","points":48,"story_id":48330192,"story_text":"Hey everyone,<p>I previously introduced an open source private home security camera in 2024, which uses OpenMLS for end-to-end encryption: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=42284412\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;news.ycombinator.com&#x2F;item?id=42284412</a>.<p>It was called Privastead then and it&#x27;s now renamed to Secluso.<p>John Kaczman found my project from here and has been working on it with me over the last year and half. We&#x27;ve made a lot of improvements to the software, which we would like to share with you:<p>- You can now set this up on your Raspberry Pi in less than 5 minutes with no technical expertise using our easy-to-use GUI deploy tool. We&#x27;ve put together a comprehensive build-your-own guide that walks you through the required steps (you can find a link at the top of the repository README).<p>- We use a customized, minimal OS based on the Yocto project for the camera.<p>- Every part of our stack except for the iOS app has reproducible builds. This includes our Android app, camera&#x2F;server binaries, deploy tool, and the aforementioned OS.<p>- We&#x27;ve re-designed our mobile app, which is now on the iOS App Store and Google Play store.<p>- We now support UnifiedPush for more privacy-preserving push notifications.<p>Looking forward to seeing what you all think!","title":"Show HN: Open-source private home security camera system (end-to-end encryption)","updated_at":"2026-05-30T07:07:09Z","url":"https://github.com/secluso/core"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"georgewsinger"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"Math-to-Manim"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://github.com/HarleyCoops/Math-To-Manim"}},"_tags":["story","author_georgewsinger","story_48293119","front_page"],"author":"georgewsinger","children":[48332576,48332612,48333221],"created_at":"2026-05-27T12:18:19Z","created_at_i":1779884299,"num_comments":5,"objectID":"48293119","points":43,"story_id":48293119,"title":"Math-to-Manim","updated_at":"2026-05-30T07:13:24Z","url":"https://github.com/HarleyCoops/Math-To-Manim"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"pseudolus"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"What It Takes to Preserve Floppy Disks"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://spectrum.ieee.org/floppy-disk-data-preservation-archives"}},"_tags":["story","author_pseudolus","story_48303623","front_page"],"author":"pseudolus","children":[48332730,48332762,48332813],"created_at":"2026-05-28T02:23:31Z","created_at_i":1779935011,"num_comments":4,"objectID":"48303623","points":28,"story_id":48303623,"title":"What It Takes to Preserve Floppy Disks","updated_at":"2026-05-30T07:10:25Z","url":"https://spectrum.ieee.org/floppy-disk-data-preservation-archives"},{"_highlightResult":{"author":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"tenderlove"},"title":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"A new register allocator for ZJIT"},"url":{"matchLevel":"none","matchedWords":[],"value":"https://railsat